The paper discusses a programming framework for serverless computing, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The framework is designed to handle dataflow and task parallelism, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions machine learning (ML) analytics, which could place it under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) or machine learning (cs.LG).
